{"id": "EUVD-2011-4031", "enisaUuid": "4a71e36b-91ee-3e11-a349-53a2a7e584fd", "description": "The sysrq_sysctl_handler function in kernel/sysctl.c in the Linux kernel before 2.6.39 does not require the CAP_SYS_ADMIN capability to modify the dmesg_restrict value, which allows local users to bypass intended access restrictions and read the kernel ring buffer by leveraging root privileges, as demonstrated by a root user in a Linux Containers (aka LXC) environment.", "datePublished": "2012-05-24T23:00:00", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-06T23:53:32", "baseScore": 4.0, "baseScoreVersion": "2.0", "baseScoreVector": "AV:L/AC:H/Au:N/C:C/I:N/A:N", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2011-4080.html", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2012:0481", "https://github.com/torvalds/linux/commit/bfdc0b497faa82a0ba2f9dddcf109231dd519fcc", "http://www.openwall.com/lists/oss-security/2011/10/26/10", "http://ftp.osuosl.org/pub/linux/kernel/v2.6/ChangeLog-2.6.39", "http://git.kernel.org/?p=linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux-2.6.git%3Ba=commit%3Bh=bfdc0b497faa82a0ba2f9dddcf109231dd519fcc"], "aliases": ["CVE-2011-4080"], "assigner": "redhat", "epss": 0.07, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "dae4b7b8-9451-304b-a91c-ffa017208805", "product": {"name": "n/a"}, "product_version": "n/a"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "5d2163ef-ac54-31ce-97a2-3fb24bd9e5a3", "vendor": {"name": "n/a"}}], "isExploited": false}